I, too had the experience of questioning villagers and asking for &quot;cam kook&quot;, altho' I thought it was &quot;cahn kook&quot;, as well as there frequent reply: &quot;hom bick&quot;, meaning, presumably, &quot; I don't understand&quot;. Also the sniper fire as we left. But what really bothers me are the wannabes that represent themselves as combat veterans who weren't. This makes it hard for me to trust any veteran until their service is verified, by the VA, for example. I know about the enemy in our midst. Thanks to all for the warm welcome; you obviously know how important that is. Thanks for the virtual hug Class Lass; it was my first:)
